extract_gbff.returns:
\code{invisible(NULL)}. This function is called for its side effects
of writing the following files to \code{workdir}:
\describe{
\item{\code{genes.csv}}{Gene feature annotation table extracted from
the GenBank file.}
\item{\code{context.txt}}{PTT-format genomic context tabular file.}
\item{\code{source.fasta}}{Raw genomic nucleotide FASTA sequences.}
\item{\code{upstream_locis.fasta}}{TSS upstream region sequences
with gene locus tag headers.}
}

extract_genomes.returns:
\code{invisible(NULL)}. This function is called for its side effects
of writing the following files for each GenBank file found:
\describe{
\item{\code{<accession_id>.faa}}{Protein FASTA file with locus-tag-only
headers.}
\item{\code{<accession_id>.csv}}{Gene feature annotation table in CSV
format.}
}

